      <title>Jimmy Rodgers</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>The front of this postcard has Jimmy Rodgers sitting, holding a double thumbs up, with a guitar in his lap. Verso reads: Jimmy Rodgers 1897-1933 Native of Meridian, Miss., known to country music fans as the "Singing rakeman" and as America's, "Blue Yodeler". T.B. shortened his railroading career and he turned to country music. Known best for songs, "Train Whistle Blues", "Down The Old Road To Home" and "Miss. Delta Blues." This photo was used for the marble memorial, now in Highland Park, Meridian, Mississippi.</abstract>
